    "version": "2.0.0",
    "description": {
      "en": "The Chronos-SCARA: a 4D Bounded Hyperobject robotic arm system.\n\nThis is not a simple CAD model — it is a parametric instantiation of a full robotic system-of-systems. Inspired by the open-source lineage of PyBot, RepRap Morgan, and ROS2-based projects, the Chronos-SCARA treats the SCARA arm as a distributed, temporal, relational entity: a Hyperobject in the sense defined by Timothy Morton.\n\nThe architecture is a hierarchy of three layers:\n1. Kinetic Layer — Aluminum-frame SCARA linkages with Strain Wave (Harmonic) Gear joints. Commercial harmonic drives maintain zero-backlash, preserving the integrity of the 4D bounded manifold.\n2. Sensory Layer (Panopticon) — Endstop anchors and Z-probe for proprioception, vision integration hooks for Visual Servoing.\n3. Kinematic Engine — Inverse Kinematics (IK) solver outputs, Singularity Manifold visualization, and a Bounded C-Space workspace envelope.\n\nOfficial Visualizer and Configurator: Yantra4D",
      "es": "El Chronos-SCARA: un sistema de brazo robótico como Hiperobjeto 4D Acotado.\n\nNo es un modelo CAD simple, sino una instanciación paramétrica de un sistema-de-sistemas robótico completo. Configurador oficial: Yantra4D"
    },
    "thumbnail": "/projects/scara-robotics.webp",
