      "material_awareness": true,
      "societal_benefit": "Democratizes precision robotic manipulation for open-source R&D and educational contexts, enabling closed-loop SCARA arms to be fabricated and maintained without commercial IP dependencies.",
      "ontological_framework": "4D Bounded Hyperobject — Chronos-SCARA exists as a distributed, temporal, relational entity across repositories, supply chains, and firmware histories. Its physical footprint is merely a local phase of a massively distributed robotic hyperobject.",
      "layers": {
        "cloud": "Git repository (URDF, Firmware Config, Vision Models) — Immortal, Non-local Memory.",
        "compute": "Raspberry Pi 5 + ROS2 Humble + Klipper Host — 4D Trajectory Planner and IK Solver.",
        "kinetic": "Aluminum-frame SCARA with commercial harmonic drives and closed-loop steppers (STM32 MCU).",
        "sensory": "Endstops, Z-probe, and vision integration hooks — the Panopticon Sensorium."
